issue.title: app_store_connect_api_key action doesn't have the api_key_path argument
issue.body:
### New Issue Checklist

- [x] Updated fastlane to the latest version
- [x] I read the [Contribution Guidelines](https://github.com/fastlane/fastlane/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md)
- [x] I read [docs.fastlane.tools](https://docs.fastlane.tools)
- [x] I searched for [existing GitHub issues](https://github.com/fastlane/fastlane/issues)

### Issue Description
app_store_connect_api_key action doesn't have the `api_key_path` option
##### Command executed

No comment


According to https://github.com/fastlane/fastlane/blob/master/fastlane/lib/fastlane/actions/app_store_connect_api_key.rb the action doesn't provide the option to log in using `api_key_path`.

All the other actions as https://github.com/fastlane/fastlane/blob/master/fastlane/lib/fastlane/actions/latest_testflight_build_number.rb or [upload_to_testflight](https://github.com/fastlane/fastlane/blob/master/fastlane/lib/fastlane/actions/upload_to_testflight.rb) provide this option.

Right now if you are using the JSON file with all the credentials inside it, you are forced to authenticate in each action indepently, since the main `app_store_connect_api_key` doesn't have this option

comment.body: what about using `key_filepath`, it seems `api_key_path` is for `cert` action

### Issue Description
app_store_connect_api_key action doesn't have the `api_key_path` option
##### Command executed

No comment


According to https://github.com/fastlane/fastlane/blob/master/fastlane/lib/fastlane/actions/app_store_connect_api_key.rb the action doesn't provide the option to log in using `api_key_path`.

All the other actions as https://github.com/fastlane/fastlane/blob/master/fastlane/lib/fastlane/actions/latest_testflight_build_number.rb or [upload_to_testflight](https://github.com/fastlane/fastlane/blob/master/fastlane/lib/fastlane/actions/upload_to_testflight.rb) provide this option.

Right now if you are using the JSON file with all the credentials inside it, you are forced to authenticate in each action indepently, since the main `app_store_connect_api_key` doesn't have this option
